extends layout

block content
  h1 Welcome to the Communities Reporter Tool REST API
  div You can interrogate the data in JSON output for the following data:

  div
    hr
    h3 DATA
    p Get community data by indicator for all years.
    p Query is based on geoids and indicator names.  For example, adding geoids=41003,41005 to the url will bring back data for those two places.  Likewise for indicators, indicators=Poverty Rate, Total Population Count.
       P For specified geoids
       ul
            li
                a(href='communityData?geoids=41003,41005,41007&indicators=Poverty Rate,Total Population Estimate&f=HTML') HTML Table
            li
                a(href='communityData?geoids=41003,41005,41007&indicators=Poverty Rate,Total Population Estimate&f=json') JSON
            li
                a(href='communityData?geoids=41003,41005,41007&indicators=Poverty Rate,Total Population Estimate&f=pjson') Pretty Print JSON
            li
                a(href='communityData?geoids=41017000100,41005,41007&indicators=Poverty Rate,Total Population Estimate&f=csv') csv
       P For specified geoType
       ul
            li
                a(href='communityData?geoType=County&indicator=Poverty Rate&f=json') JSON
            li
                a(href='communityData?geoType=County&indicator=Poverty Rate&f=pjson') Pretty Print JSON
       P With metadata for 'basic' view
       ul
            li
                a(href='communityData?geoids=41003,41005&indicator=Poverty Rate&viewType=basic&f=json') JSON
            li
                a(href='communityData?geoids=41003,41005&indicator=Poverty Rate&viewType=basic&f=pjson') Pretty Print JSON
       P Drilldown Data by Subtopic for GEOID
       ul
            li
                a(href='communityData?drilldown=1&subtopic=Poverty Rate&geoid=41003&f=json') JSON
            li
                a(href='communityData?drilldown=1&subtopic=Poverty Rate&geoid=41003&f=pjson') Pretty Print JSON

  hr
  div
    h3 GEOJSON
    p Get a geojson response for selected place type and year span
        ul
            li
                a(href='geojson?placeType=Counties&years=2010') JSON
  hr
  div
    h3 PLACES
    p Get list of places or specify a place to get more details about it.
    p For example, adding place=Corvallis to the url will bring back a description for the place Corvallis.
       p ALL PLACES
       ul
            li
                a(href='places?term=Cor&f=HTML') HTML Table
            li
                a(href='places?term=Cor&f=json') JSON
            li
                a(href='places?term=Cor&f=pjson') Pretty Print JSON
       p Place Information (Geo shift, county, school district, years)
       ul
            li
                a(href='places?place=Corvallis&geoid=4115800&geoType=Incorporated City&f=HTML') HTML Table
            li
                a(href='places?place=Corvallis&geoid=4115800&geoType=Incorporated City&f=json') JSON
            li
                a(href='places?place=Corvallis&geoid=4115800&geoType=Incorporated City&f=pjson') Pretty Print JSON
  hr
  div
    h3 PLACES TYPES - Geo Years
    p Get results for each place type with what geo years it needs (for geojson).
       ul
            li
                a(href='placetypes&f=json') JSON
            li
                a(href='placetypes&f=pjson') Pretty Print JSON
  hr
  div
    h3 INDICATORS
    p Get community data by indicator for all years.
    p Query is based on geoids and indicator names.  For example, adding geoids=41003,41005 to the url will bring back data for those two places.  Likewise for indicators, indicators=Poverty Rate, Total Population Count.
       p LIST
       ul
            li
                a(href='indicators?f=HTML') HTML Table
            li
                a(href='indicators?f=json') JSON
            li
                a(href='indicators?f=pjson') Pretty Print JSON
       p LIST (DEEP)
       ul
            li
                a(href='indicators?deep=true&f=HTML') HTML Table
            li
                a(href='indicators?deep=true&f=json') JSON
            li
                a(href='indicators?deep=true&f=pjson') Pretty Print JSON
       p LIST BY TOPIC(S)
       ul
            li
                a(href='indicators?topics=Population&f=HTML') HTML Table
            li
                a(href='indicators?topics=Population&f=json') JSON
            li
                a(href='indicators?topics=Population&f=pjson') Pretty Print JSON
       p INDICATOR INFO
       ul
            li
                a(href='indicators?indicator=Total Population Count&f=HTML') HTML Table
            li
                a(href='indicators?indicator=Poverty Rate&f=json') JSON
            li
                a(href='indicators?indicator=Poverty Rate&f=pjson') Pretty Print JSON
       p FEATURED INDICATORS
       ul
            li
                a(href='indicators?featured&f=HTML') HTML Table
            li
                a(href='indicators?featured&f=json') JSON
            li
                a(href='indicators?featured&f=pjson') Pretty Print JSON

  hr
  div
    h3 TOPICS
    p Get a list of all OLD topics.
         ul
            li
                a(href='topics?f=HTML') HTML Table
            li
                a(href='topics?f=json') JSON
            li
                a(href='topics?f=pjson') Pretty Print JSON
    p Get a list of all CRT (NEW) topics.
       ul
            li
                a(href='topics?crt=true&f=HTML') HTML Table
            li
                a(href='topics?crt=true&f=json') JSON
            li
                a(href='topics?crt=true&f=pjson') Pretty Print JSON
  hr
  div
    h3 COLLECTIONS
    p Get list of collections.  A collection is a sponsored subset of indicators to highlight collection specific themes.
       ul
            li
                a(href='collections?f=HTML') HTML Table
            li
                a(href='collections?f=json') JSON
            li
                a(href='collections?f=pjson') Pretty Print JSON

  div
    h3 SCHOOL DATA
    p Get school data by school district or school.
       ul
            li
                a(href='schools?schooldistrict=1&schooldists=Corvallis SD 509J,Statewide&indicator=Percentage of 3rd Graders who met Reading Requirement&f=html') HTML Table
            li
                a(href='schools?schooldistrict=1&schooldists=Corvallis SD 509J,Statewide&indicator=Percentage of 3rd Graders who met Reading Requirement&f=json') JSON
            li
                a(href='schools?schooldistrict=1&schooldists=Corvallis SD 509J,Statewide&indicator=Percentage of 3rd Graders who met Reading Requirement&f=pjson') Pretty Print JSON

  div
    h3 REPORTS
    p Downloadable reports for Admin Tool
       ul
            li
                a(href='reports?reportType=year_indicators&year=1990&f=csv') All indicators for 1990 as CSV
            li
                a(href='reports?reportType=year_variables&year=1990&f=csv') All variable data records for 1990 as CSV
            li
                a(href='reports?reportType=all_year_indicator&varIndicator=Total%20Population%20Estimate&f=csv') Add data for indicator Total Population Estimate as CSV
            li
                a(href='reports?reportType=all_year_variable&varIndicator=%23%205%2B%20in%20linguistically%20isolated%20HHs&f=csv') All data for variable data # 5+ in linguistically isolated HHs as CSV